      <option id="A">Longitudinal</option>
      <option id="B">Transverse</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Cannot be polarized.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Does the power factor of a circuit depend on frequency of the source?</text>
      <option id="A">Yes (through Xl and Xc)</option>
      <option id="B">No</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>cos φ = R / √[R^2 + (ωL - 1/ωC)^2].</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Smallest possible charge which can exist independently is ____.</text>
      <option id="A">Charge of electron (e)</option>
      <option id="B">Quark charge (e/3)?? No, not independently.</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Millikan's discovery.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Which of the following is an extensive property?</text>
      <option id="A">Enthalpy</option>
      <option id="B">Temperature</option>
      <option id="C">Pressure</option>
      
      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Depends on amount of substance.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Presence of -I group ____ the basic strength of amines.</text>
      <option id="A">Decreases</option>
      <option id="B">Increases</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Reduces lone pair availability.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>The substance that is adsorbed on the surface is called ____.</text>
      <option id="A">Adsorbate</option>
      <option id="B">Adsorbent</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Like a solute in a solution.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Phosphine (PH3) has a bond angle of about 93.6°. This suggests that the p-orbitals ____.</text>
      <option id="A">Are nearly pure p-orbitals without much hybridization</option>
      <option id="B">Are sp2 hybridized</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Drago's rule explains why heavier hydrides show little hybridization.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Is Z = 5 min(x,y) a linear objective function?</text>
      <option id="A">No</option>
      <option id="B">Yes</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>min() function introduces non-linearity (change in slope).</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Metallurgy of silver: Displacement of silver from [Ag(CN)2]- is a ____ reaction.</text>
      <option id="A">Redox (Displacement)</option>
      <option id="B">Neutralization</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Zn (0) -&gt; Zn (+2), Ag (+1) -&gt; Ag (0).</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Libermann's Nitroso test is used for ____ amines.</text>
      <option id="A">Secondary (2°)</option>
      <option id="B">Primary</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Gives yellow oily nitrosoamine.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Odds against student passing 3:7. Odds against student B passing 3:5. Independent. P(Both pass):</text>
      <option id="A">7/10 * 5/8 = 7/16</option>
      <option id="B">3/10</option>
      <option id="C">1/16</option>
      
